result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander Moss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexander Moss in court with attorney Brian Christopher Hagner.  Defendant Alexander Moss in custody.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
cab
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
As to counts 1 and 2:
Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction as to count 1 and 3 months in the House of Correction as to count 2, consecutive to each other and any other sentence, with credit for -0- days served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 years, concurrent with each other and the sentence the defendant is serving,  with the following conditions:
- Serve 60 days in the House of Correction as to count 1; STAYED pending review.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random urine screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim unless approved by the court.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay DV surcharge, DNA surcharge plus all other costs and surcharges; civil judgment if not paid.
- Pay supervision fees.

Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
The next court date is in Branch 36.
  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for February 19, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
